- The integer array parameter `arr` must not be null.
- The boolean result is true if there is a cycle in the integer array `arr`.
- The boolean result is false if there is no cycle in the integer array `arr`.
- The cycle in the array consists of a sequence of indices `seq` of length `k` where every `arr[seq[j]]` is either all positive or all negative.
- The length of the cycle `k` must be greater than 1.
- The length of the integer array `arr` is between 1 and 5000.
- The values in the integer array `arr` are between -1000 and 1000, and not equal to 0.